<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to
                                Baron <persName type="to">Ketteler</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-10-19"><hi rend="italic">October 19,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge, with
                            thanks, the receipt of your note of the 7th instant, inclosing a
                            memorandum relative to the views of the Imperial German Government in
                            regard to a difference of opinion which has recently arisen between the
                            consular board and the municipal council at Apia with regard to the
                            appointment of returning officers for municipal elections.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>